1
00:00:01,001 --> 00:00:02,711
<b>-[Beth] </b><i><b>Are you on your way home?</b></i>
<b>-[gasps]</b>

2
00:00:02,794 --> 00:00:04,295
<i><b>Anton is dead!</b></i>

3
00:00:06,297 --> 00:00:08,508
<i><b>You did this, huh?</b></i>
<i><b>Why are you doing this?!</b></i>

4
00:00:08,591 --> 00:00:09,843
<i><b>I'm getting my revenge.</b></i>

5
00:00:09,926 --> 00:00:11,594
<i><b>And you will pay.</b></i>

6
00:00:11,678 --> 00:00:14,389
<i><b>If Anton was killed here,</b></i>
<i><b>there should be more blood.</b></i>

7
00:00:14,472 --> 00:00:16,433
<i><b>This means he was killed somewhere else.</b></i>

8
00:00:16,516 --> 00:00:18,977
<i><b>I’m swallowing all my pride, Erica.</b></i>

9
00:00:19,060 --> 00:00:20,812
<i><b>Please help my husband.</b></i>

10
00:00:20,895 --> 00:00:22,564
<i><b>Erica, about what you said before,</b></i>

11
00:00:22,647 --> 00:00:25,108
<i><b>I’m ready to tell</b></i>
<i><b>everyone what we did to Edong.</b></i>

12
00:00:25,191 --> 00:00:27,027
<i><b>I don’t think that will make</b></i>
<i><b>any difference anymore, Beth.</b></i>

13
00:00:27,110 --> 00:00:29,529
<i><b>The only thing we can do</b></i>
<i><b>now is find him and stop him.</b></i>

14
00:00:29,612 --> 00:00:31,573
<i><b>Erica, I don't want to do this for Edong.</b></i>

15
00:00:31,656 --> 00:00:32,615
<i><b>I'm doing this for myself.</b></i>

16
00:00:32,699 --> 00:00:35,410
<i><b>Prosecutor, we would</b></i>
<i><b>like to present to you the original source</b></i>

17
00:00:35,493 --> 00:00:38,204
<i><b>of the video sent to</b></i>
<i><b>Edgar Mattos' girlfriend.</b></i>

18
00:00:38,288 --> 00:00:40,290
<i><b>This includes the complete</b></i>
<i><b>video with its original metadata.</b></i>

19
00:00:40,373 --> 00:00:43,001
<i><b>The truth is right in front of us,</b></i>

20
00:00:43,084 --> 00:00:44,335
<i><b>and we’re still pinning this crime on him.</b></i>

21
00:00:44,419 --> 00:00:47,046
<i><b>Let’s call it by it's real name,</b></i>
<i><b>injustice.</b></i>

22
00:00:47,130 --> 00:00:48,173
<i><b>My love!</b></i>

23
00:00:48,256 --> 00:00:50,008
<i><b>Erica, thank you so much.</b></i>

24
00:00:50,091 --> 00:00:51,426
<i><b>I can never repay you.</b></i>

25
00:00:51,509 --> 00:00:52,844
<i><b>It's game time.</b></i>

26
00:00:55,638 --> 00:01:02,228
<b>[theme music playing]</b>

27
00:02:11,631 --> 00:02:18,596
<b>-[indistinct chatter]</b>
<b>-[cameras clicking]</b>

28
00:02:23,685 --> 00:02:25,770
<b>-Yeah, I know.</b>
<b>-[Erica sighs softly]</b>

29
00:02:26,729 --> 00:02:28,273
<b>[chatter stops]</b>

30
00:02:28,356 --> 00:02:29,983
<b>-[cameras click]</b>
<b>-[Erica inhales deeply]</b>

31
00:02:30,066 --> 00:02:32,152
<b>We asked you all to come here today</b>

32
00:02:33,153 --> 00:02:34,988
<b>to give a statement</b>

33
00:02:35,071 --> 00:02:37,115
<b>about the death of Anton Montenegro,</b>

34
00:02:38,032 --> 00:02:40,910
<b>and an incident</b>
<b>that happened 14 years ago.</b>

35
00:02:40,994 --> 00:02:45,623
<b>As you may have heard,</b>
<b>yesterday my client, Ryan Mora,</b>

36
00:02:45,707 --> 00:02:48,167
<b>who is the husband of my friend Beth,</b>

37
00:02:48,251 --> 00:02:51,212
<b>became a suspect in</b>
<b>the murder of Anton Montenegro.</b>

38
00:02:51,296 --> 00:02:54,632
<b>His body, along with the murder weapon,</b>

39
00:02:54,716 --> 00:02:56,301
<b>were found inside Ryan's shop.</b>

40
00:02:56,384 --> 00:02:58,511
<b>But my client is innocent.</b>

41
00:02:58,595 --> 00:03:02,849
<b>Autopsy reports prove</b>
<b>that Anton was dead for two hours</b>

42
00:03:02,932 --> 00:03:05,435
<b>when they found</b>
<b>his body inside Ryan's shop.</b>

43
00:03:05,518 --> 00:03:07,478
<b>What happened was clearly a setup.</b>

44
00:03:07,562 --> 00:03:10,106
<b>That's why the case</b>
<b>has was dismissed a minute ago</b>

45
00:03:10,189 --> 00:03:11,900
<b>and Ryan is here now.</b>

46
00:03:12,775 --> 00:03:15,069
<b>[cameras clicking]</b>

47
00:03:15,153 --> 00:03:17,363
<b>[solemn music playing]</b>

48
00:03:18,031 --> 00:03:20,158
<b>What does this case</b>
<b>have to do with the incident</b>

49
00:03:20,241 --> 00:03:21,701
<b>that happened 14 years ago, Attorney?</b>

50
00:03:22,785 --> 00:03:26,873
<b>We are certain</b>
<b>we know who really killed Anton.</b>

51
00:03:26,956 --> 00:03:29,751
<b>In fact, I'm sure</b>
<b>you all know him as well.</b>

52
00:03:29,834 --> 00:03:33,171
<b>It's the escaped convict Edong Santiago,</b>

53
00:03:33,254 --> 00:03:37,050
<b>who also went to prison</b>
<b>for the murder of Louisa Soria.</b>

54
00:03:37,133 --> 00:03:39,010
<b>-Edong Santiago?</b>
<b>-Edong Santiago?</b>

55
00:03:43,097 --> 00:03:45,099
<b>We were in our senior year of high school.</b>

56
00:03:45,183 --> 00:03:48,186
<b>We were 16, 17 years old.</b>

57
00:03:48,269 --> 00:03:49,687
<b>-[Louisa] </b><i><b>No!</b></i>
<b>-[thunder crashes]</b>

58
00:03:49,771 --> 00:03:50,897
<i><b>Louisa!</b></i>

59
00:03:50,980 --> 00:03:54,192
<b>[Erica] We didn't just find Louisa's body.</b>

60
00:03:54,275 --> 00:03:57,237
<b>We witnessed her murder firsthand.</b>

61
00:03:57,320 --> 00:04:00,365
<b>Then we came face to face with her killer.</b>

62
00:04:00,448 --> 00:04:03,159
<b>We tried to stop them from escaping,</b>

63
00:04:03,243 --> 00:04:05,286
<b>but we never saw their face.</b>

64
00:04:05,370 --> 00:04:08,665
<b>[Alice] Of course,</b>
<b>we were considered witnesses.</b>

65
00:04:08,748 --> 00:04:10,124
<b>We tried our best</b>

66
00:04:10,208 --> 00:04:13,628
<b>to recall the events as</b>
<b>detailed as possible, but…</b>

67
00:04:15,797 --> 00:04:18,424
<b>…what we couldn't give was a name.</b>

68
00:04:19,717 --> 00:04:23,263
<b>And… [sighs sharply]</b>
<b>…during the course of the investigation,</b>

69
00:04:24,138 --> 00:04:26,140
<b>a witness testified.</b>

70
00:04:26,224 --> 00:04:30,728
<b>And that witness identified Edong.</b>

71
00:04:30,812 --> 00:04:33,982
<b>That witness was Esther Castro.</b>

72
00:04:37,360 --> 00:04:39,445
<b>Even though we insisted that</b>

73
00:04:39,529 --> 00:04:41,781
<b>we didn't see the killer's face,</b>

74
00:04:41,864 --> 00:04:43,992
<b>the officer in charge of the investigation</b>

75
00:04:44,075 --> 00:04:46,411
<b>kept insisting that it was Edong.</b>

76
00:04:46,494 --> 00:04:49,205
<b>He wanted us to</b>
<b>agree with Esther's statement.</b>

77
00:04:49,289 --> 00:04:52,875
<b>And that officer is Rodrigo Celestino.</b>

78
00:04:52,959 --> 00:04:57,714
<b>[solemn music continues]</b>

79
00:05:06,264 --> 00:05:07,432
<b>[clears throat]</b>

80
00:05:14,063 --> 00:05:17,191
<b>Celestino wouldn't leave us alone.</b>

81
00:05:17,275 --> 00:05:19,610
<b>On top of pressuring us,</b>
<b>he also threatened us</b>

82
00:05:19,694 --> 00:05:22,280
<b>and threw baseless accusations at us.</b>

83
00:05:22,363 --> 00:05:26,034
<b>And when everything</b>
<b>that happened spread across Amurao,</b>

84
00:05:26,701 --> 00:05:29,162
<b>the people started to pressure us too</b>

85
00:05:29,245 --> 00:05:31,331
<b>into blaming Edong.</b>

86
00:05:33,541 --> 00:05:34,542
<b>[sighs]</b>

87
00:05:36,085 --> 00:05:37,086
<b>So…</b>

88
00:05:38,379 --> 00:05:41,382
<b>when the police found</b>
<b>a watch in Edong’s things</b>

89
00:05:41,466 --> 00:05:43,259
<b>that looked like Louisa’s,</b>

90
00:05:43,342 --> 00:05:45,219
<b>even though it wasn’t really hers,</b>

91
00:05:45,303 --> 00:05:46,846
<b>we said…</b>

92
00:05:50,099 --> 00:05:57,065
<b>[solemn music continues, fades]</b>

93
00:05:58,399 --> 00:06:00,026
<b>Actually, I said…</b>

94
00:06:01,527 --> 00:06:03,154
<b>that it belonged to Louisa.</b>

95
00:06:04,155 --> 00:06:07,241
<b>Mel and Alice corroborated the story.</b>

96
00:06:08,826 --> 00:06:10,244
<b>This led to Edong’s conviction.</b>

97
00:06:11,496 --> 00:06:13,456
<b>-[reporter 1] Huh?</b>
<b>-Are you saying,</b>

98
00:06:13,539 --> 00:06:15,792
<b>you lied about the watch?</b>

99
00:06:15,875 --> 00:06:22,632
<b>[solemn music resumes]</b>

100
00:06:25,134 --> 00:06:26,344
<b>-Yes.</b>
<b>-[reporters gasp]</b>

101
00:06:26,427 --> 00:06:27,929
<b>I lied.</b>

102
00:06:29,722 --> 00:06:33,976
<b>And your friends went along with this lie?</b>

103
00:06:34,060 --> 00:06:39,440
<b>[solemn music continues]</b>

104
00:06:39,524 --> 00:06:41,442
<b>-Yes.</b>
<b>-Mm-hmm.</b>

105
00:06:41,526 --> 00:06:43,236
<b>-Seriously?</b>
<b>-Oh my god.</b>

106
00:06:43,319 --> 00:06:44,779
<b>-How could they do that?</b>
<b>-[Beth sniffles]</b>

107
00:06:44,862 --> 00:06:46,447
<b>-Really?</b>
<b>-Oh my god.</b>

108
00:06:46,531 --> 00:06:49,033
<b>We supported her statement.</b>

109
00:06:49,117 --> 00:06:53,079
<b>Actually, I forced Erica not to speak up.</b>

110
00:06:55,581 --> 00:06:58,209
<b>-[reporter 2] So is Edong innocent?</b>
<b>-[music fades]</b>

111
00:07:00,711 --> 00:07:04,340
<b>[unsettling music playing]</b>

112
00:07:04,423 --> 00:07:06,717
<b>Because of that lie,</b>

113
00:07:07,927 --> 00:07:10,054
<b>Edong went to jail.</b>

114
00:07:10,847 --> 00:07:13,099
<b>And the reason he escaped</b>

115
00:07:13,933 --> 00:07:16,185
<b>was to get his revenge on us.</b>

116
00:07:16,269 --> 00:07:17,895
<b>On me.</b>

117
00:07:17,979 --> 00:07:21,691
<b>That's why he killed Mel's husband,</b>
<b>Anton Montenegro.</b>

118
00:07:22,525 --> 00:07:26,195
<b>And why he’s trying to frame my husband.</b>

119
00:07:27,280 --> 00:07:29,615
<b>[reporter 3] So you sent</b>
<b>an innocent person to jail?</b>

120
00:07:29,699 --> 00:07:35,621
<b>[unsettling music continues]</b>

121
00:07:37,373 --> 00:07:40,585
<b>I've long believed</b>
<b>that Edong Santiago is innocent.</b>

122
00:07:43,045 --> 00:07:44,714
<b>But to this day,</b>

123
00:07:45,298 --> 00:07:47,675
<b>I still haven't been able to prove it.</b>

124
00:07:50,720 --> 00:07:51,846
<b>[man 1] Dude, look.</b>

125
00:07:52,680 --> 00:07:53,973
<b>Do I look like Edong?</b>

126
00:07:54,849 --> 00:07:58,227
<b>What if I stalk Chona outside her house?</b>

127
00:07:58,311 --> 00:07:59,812
<b>I bet she'd piss herself scared.</b>

128
00:07:59,896 --> 00:08:01,814
<b>Serves her right for turning me down.</b>

129
00:08:01,898 --> 00:08:03,524
<b>[man 2] Fuck, dude!</b>

130
00:08:03,608 --> 00:08:07,445
<b>That damn</b>
<b>Attorney Erica and friends admitted</b>

131
00:08:07,528 --> 00:08:09,947
<b>they lied about Edong.</b>

132
00:08:10,031 --> 00:08:11,949
<b>-Look.</b>
<b>-Shit, really, dude?</b>

133
00:08:12,033 --> 00:08:14,118
<b>[man 1] I knew it! Edong for president.</b>

134
00:08:14,202 --> 00:08:15,745
<b>-Edong for president!</b>
<b>-Edong for president!</b>

135
00:08:17,205 --> 00:08:19,457
<b>[woman] Stop that nonsense!</b>

136
00:08:19,540 --> 00:08:23,920
<b>That man killed a lot of people!</b>
<b>How could you want a president like that?</b>

137
00:08:24,003 --> 00:08:26,422
<b>You two are scum just like him!</b>

138
00:08:26,506 --> 00:08:30,134
<b>Go scram to the plaza!</b>
<b>Stop spreading your nonsense here!</b>

139
00:08:30,218 --> 00:08:34,555
<b>That's why Edong is</b>
<b>on a killing spree in Amurao.</b>

140
00:08:34,639 --> 00:08:36,307
<b>Because they screwed him over before,</b>

141
00:08:36,390 --> 00:08:38,643
<b>just like what you are doing to us now.</b>

142
00:08:38,726 --> 00:08:40,520
<b>That's why we're on Edong's side.</b>

143
00:08:40,603 --> 00:08:41,854
<b>[man 1] We are one with Edong!</b>

144
00:08:41,938 --> 00:08:43,814
<b>[both chanting] We are one with Edong!</b>

145
00:08:43,898 --> 00:08:45,233
<b>-We are one with Edong!</b>
<b>-Oh, whatever.</b>

146
00:08:45,316 --> 00:08:46,984
<b>-[woman] Suit yourselves!</b>
<b>-We are one with Edong!</b>

147
00:08:47,068 --> 00:08:49,278
<b>-We are one with Edong!</b>
<b>-[Edong laughing]</b>

148
00:08:49,362 --> 00:08:51,656
<b>[woman] Oh,</b>
<b>whatever! Go side with that killer!</b>

149
00:08:51,739 --> 00:08:52,907
<b>[man 2] We sure will!</b>

150
00:08:52,990 --> 00:08:54,116
<b>[man 1] We will, lady!</b>

151
00:08:54,200 --> 00:08:55,451
<b>We're on Edong's side!</b>

152
00:08:55,535 --> 00:08:56,494
<b>[man 2] Yeah!</b>

153
00:08:57,203 --> 00:08:58,371
<b>[reporter 4] </b><i><b>After fourteen years,</b></i>

154
00:08:58,454 --> 00:09:00,665
<i><b>why do you want to</b></i>
<i><b>speak out now, Attorney?</b></i>

155
00:09:00,748 --> 00:09:03,626
<b>Why hold this press conference?</b>

156
00:09:04,377 --> 00:09:06,796
<b>[inhales, exhales heavily]</b>

157
00:09:07,964 --> 00:09:11,092
<b>Because that lie held us</b>
<b>hostage for fourteen years.</b>

158
00:09:11,801 --> 00:09:13,219
<b>We were tortured.</b>

159
00:09:13,302 --> 00:09:14,929
<b>Silenced.</b>

160
00:09:15,012 --> 00:09:16,764
<b>We had to live with guilt,</b>

161
00:09:17,390 --> 00:09:18,599
<b>shame,</b>

162
00:09:19,141 --> 00:09:20,184
<b>and regret.</b>

163
00:09:22,186 --> 00:09:25,439
<b>But we're not the ones who need freedom.</b>

164
00:09:26,816 --> 00:09:28,526
<b>The one who should be freed</b>

165
00:09:28,609 --> 00:09:31,737
<b>is the person</b>
<b>who was imprisoned for that lie.</b>

166
00:09:31,821 --> 00:09:34,657
<b>-Who could it be?</b>
<b>-What does she mean?</b>

167
00:09:35,366 --> 00:09:37,785
<b>-[somber music playing]</b>
<b>-[inhales deeply]</b>

168
00:09:37,868 --> 00:09:39,829
<b>Edong, if you're watching…</b>

169
00:09:41,789 --> 00:09:43,916
<b>Set yourself free.</b>

170
00:09:45,042 --> 00:09:46,711
<b>Not only for us,</b>

171
00:09:47,628 --> 00:09:49,797
<b>but also for yourself and your brother.</b>

172
00:09:49,880 --> 00:09:52,592
<b>-[music becomes dramatic]</b>
<b>-We know that, among all of us,</b>

173
00:09:52,675 --> 00:09:55,845
<b>you're the one most</b>
<b>deeply affected by this tragedy.</b>

174
00:09:55,928 --> 00:10:00,016
<b>Even though we were</b>
<b>surrounded by fear and shame,</b>

175
00:10:00,099 --> 00:10:03,144
<b>you've carried the heaviest burden.</b>

176
00:10:03,227 --> 00:10:04,687
<b>But now,</b>

177
00:10:06,314 --> 00:10:07,982
<b>we're rewriting the story.</b>

178
00:10:08,065 --> 00:10:09,233
<b>[dramatic music continues]</b>

179
00:10:09,317 --> 00:10:11,402
<b>We've been trying to</b>
<b>correct the mistake of the past.</b>

180
00:10:12,778 --> 00:10:13,904
<b>Because of you.</b>

181
00:10:14,530 --> 00:10:17,700
<b>You have shown us</b>
<b>that we cannot remain silent.</b>

182
00:10:18,576 --> 00:10:21,203
<b>We have to stand up for what is right.</b>

183
00:10:22,913 --> 00:10:24,290
<b>I hope you do, too.</b>

184
00:10:24,373 --> 00:10:26,626
<b>It's not too late, Edong.</b>

185
00:10:26,709 --> 00:10:28,419
<b>[dramatic music continues]</b>

186
00:10:28,502 --> 00:10:30,212
<b>The story is not over yet.</b>

187
00:10:31,505 --> 00:10:36,677
<b>We can still write</b>
<b>a happy ending to all of this.</b>

188
00:10:36,761 --> 00:10:38,512
<b>[music fades]</b>

189
00:10:38,596 --> 00:10:40,973
<b>[birds chirping]</b>

190
00:10:51,859 --> 00:10:55,279
<b>[pensive music playing]</b>

191
00:10:57,448 --> 00:11:02,912
<b>[pensive music swells]</b>

192
00:11:13,214 --> 00:11:15,007
<b>[chirping continues]</b>

193
00:11:15,091 --> 00:11:19,470
<b>[music turns ominous]</b>

194
00:11:22,640 --> 00:11:23,349
<b>[car door closes]</b>

195
00:11:23,432 --> 00:11:26,894
<b>The police are currently ensuing</b>
<b>a manhunt for Edong Santiago.</b>

196
00:11:26,977 --> 00:11:29,355
<b>We're just waiting to</b>
<b>hear an update from them.</b>

197
00:11:29,438 --> 00:11:31,899
<b>-[reporter 5] Okay.</b>
<b>-Of course, we have to give Mel…</b>

198
00:11:31,982 --> 00:11:34,235
<b>[indistinct chatter]</b>

199
00:11:34,318 --> 00:11:36,278
<b>[Erica] … because</b>
<b>her husband just passed.</b>

200
00:11:37,154 --> 00:11:40,533
<b>I'm sorry, but please</b>
<b>give them some space for now.</b>

201
00:11:40,616 --> 00:11:42,410
<b>There'll be time for questions soon.</b>

202
00:11:44,620 --> 00:11:46,080
<b>Thanks. Thank you.</b>

203
00:11:46,747 --> 00:11:47,915
<b>Thank you, Auntie.</b>

204
00:11:50,126 --> 00:11:51,252
<b>Love.</b>

205
00:11:51,335 --> 00:11:53,170
<b>You were so brave earlier.</b>

206
00:11:53,254 --> 00:11:54,338
<b>Really?</b>

207
00:11:55,005 --> 00:11:57,216
<b>With all the mistakes I've made,</b>

208
00:11:57,299 --> 00:11:59,343
<b>I know it's not enough</b>
<b>to make up for everything.</b>

209
00:11:59,427 --> 00:12:02,304
<b>[melancholic music playing]</b>

210
00:12:02,388 --> 00:12:03,764
<b>Sweetheart.</b>

211
00:12:03,848 --> 00:12:05,641
<b>You know, I did that</b>

212
00:12:05,724 --> 00:12:10,187
<b>to show you that</b>
<b>I'm taking responsibility for what I did.</b>

213
00:12:10,271 --> 00:12:12,231
<b>I'm sorry, okay?</b>

214
00:12:12,314 --> 00:12:14,900
<b>I got defensive while</b>
<b>talking about it with you.</b>

215
00:12:15,860 --> 00:12:17,111
<b>[sighs deeply]</b>

216
00:12:17,194 --> 00:12:18,362
<b>I hope…</b>

217
00:12:19,530 --> 00:12:21,740
<b>I hope, even just a little,</b>

218
00:12:21,824 --> 00:12:25,744
<b>you'll find yourself trusting me again.</b>

219
00:12:25,828 --> 00:12:27,746
<b>[melancholic music continues]</b>

220
00:12:27,830 --> 00:12:28,998
<b>I promise you this.</b>

221
00:12:29,081 --> 00:12:30,916
<b>I'll spend my whole life making amends.</b>

222
00:12:31,000 --> 00:12:33,836
<b>This is character</b>
<b>development until the very end.</b>

223
00:12:36,464 --> 00:12:37,798
<b>Mama.</b>

224
00:12:37,882 --> 00:12:40,259
<b>I still believe in you.</b>

225
00:12:40,926 --> 00:12:42,761
<b>I know,</b>

226
00:12:42,845 --> 00:12:45,764
<b>it was very hard for</b>
<b>you to say that out loud.</b>

227
00:12:46,640 --> 00:12:48,559
<b>But you did it.</b>

228
00:12:48,642 --> 00:12:50,394
<b>[sniffles]</b>

229
00:12:50,478 --> 00:12:51,979
<b>And you super slayed.</b>

230
00:12:52,062 --> 00:12:53,647
<b>[Ryan, Chloe chuckle]</b>

231
00:12:53,731 --> 00:12:57,526
<b>-It's giving, iconic!</b>
<b>-[all laugh]</b>

232
00:12:59,862 --> 00:13:01,197
<b>Thank you, dear.</b>

233
00:13:01,697 --> 00:13:02,490
<b>[sniffles]</b>

234
00:13:02,573 --> 00:13:10,498
<b>[melancholic music continues]</b>

235
00:13:20,174 --> 00:13:22,009
<b>[music fades]</b>

236
00:13:22,092 --> 00:13:23,928
<b>[indistinct chatter]</b>

237
00:13:24,011 --> 00:13:27,306
<b>[foreboding music playing]</b>

238
00:13:29,266 --> 00:13:32,186
<b>[birds chirping]</b>

239
00:13:38,192 --> 00:13:43,739
<b>[music becomes suspenseful]</b>

240
00:13:49,578 --> 00:13:50,704
<b>Edong!</b>

241
00:13:51,330 --> 00:13:52,289
<b>Edong!</b>

242
00:13:52,373 --> 00:13:55,292
<b>[panting]</b>

243
00:13:55,960 --> 00:13:56,669
<b>[man grunts]</b>

244
00:13:57,378 --> 00:13:58,379
<b>Edong!</b>

245
00:13:58,462 --> 00:13:59,088
<b>[man grunts weakly]</b>

246
00:14:00,256 --> 00:14:01,590
<b>[groans]</b>

247
00:14:04,218 --> 00:14:05,511
<b>-[both grunting]</b>
<b>-[bodies thud]</b>

248
00:14:08,430 --> 00:14:09,932
<b>Damn it! You?!</b>

249
00:14:10,891 --> 00:14:12,142
<b>[Dolores wailing]</b>

250
00:14:12,226 --> 00:14:13,394
<i><b>-Well?</b></i>
<i><b>-Stop it, Papa!</b></i>

251
00:14:13,477 --> 00:14:14,812
<b>-[loud thwack]</b>
<b>-[objects clatter, shatter]</b>

252
00:14:14,895 --> 00:14:16,230
<i><b>Stay out of this!</b></i>

253
00:14:16,313 --> 00:14:17,898
<i><b>Lucas!</b></i>

254
00:14:17,982 --> 00:14:19,608
<i><b>Oh my! Lucas!</b></i>

255
00:14:19,692 --> 00:14:21,735
<b>[breathing heavily]</b>

256
00:14:21,819 --> 00:14:23,404
<b>[suspenseful music continues]</b>

257
00:14:23,487 --> 00:14:24,822
<b>[Crisanto grunts]</b>

258
00:14:28,117 --> 00:14:29,410
<b>[grunts]</b>

259
00:14:29,493 --> 00:14:31,495
<b>-[blow lands]</b>
<b>-[groans, coughing]</b>

260
00:14:36,834 --> 00:14:41,672
<b>[ominous music playing]</b>

261
00:14:41,755 --> 00:14:43,883
<b>-[stirring music playing]</b>
<b>-[telephone ringing]</b>

262
00:14:47,344 --> 00:14:48,637
<b>Where is he?</b>

263
00:14:49,930 --> 00:14:56,937
<b>[music becomes pensive]</b>

264
00:14:59,315 --> 00:15:00,983
<i><b>You just won't stop, huh?</b></i>

265
00:15:01,650 --> 00:15:03,986
<i><b>I told you. I don't know where she is.</b></i>

266
00:15:04,069 --> 00:15:05,738
<i><b>Shouldn't you already know that?</b></i>

267
00:15:05,821 --> 00:15:08,532
<i><b>My mother's sick.</b></i>
<i><b>We don't need this harassment.</b></i>

268
00:15:08,616 --> 00:15:10,659
<b>[Marco] </b><i><b>The mother and son.</b></i>
<i><b>They couldn't trace them?</b></i>

269
00:15:10,743 --> 00:15:14,496
<i><b>I have a feeling that Edong got</b></i>
<i><b>Esther's location from them.</b></i>

270
00:15:14,580 --> 00:15:17,833
<i><b>They were murdered</b></i>
<i><b>after Edong got what he wanted.</b></i>

271
00:15:17,917 --> 00:15:19,752
<i><b>They died before Esther.</b></i>

272
00:15:19,835 --> 00:15:21,629
<i><b>What about Esther's sick sister?</b></i>

273
00:15:21,712 --> 00:15:23,047
<i><b>Her nephew?</b></i>

274
00:15:23,130 --> 00:15:25,215
<i><b>Edong attacked them at home,</b></i>

275
00:15:25,299 --> 00:15:27,551
<i><b>and to this day, they're still missing.</b></i>

276
00:15:27,635 --> 00:15:29,929
<i><b>What did they do wrong, Lucas?</b></i>

277
00:15:30,012 --> 00:15:33,182
<i><b>If he kills innocent people,</b></i>

278
00:15:33,849 --> 00:15:36,226
<i><b>how can anyone call that justice?</b></i>

279
00:15:36,310 --> 00:15:40,105
<b>[pensive music continues, ends]</b>

280
00:15:40,189 --> 00:15:41,398
<b>-Come on!</b>
<b>-[grunts]</b>

281
00:15:41,482 --> 00:15:43,400
<b>Hang on! Where are you taking me?!</b>

282
00:15:44,526 --> 00:15:47,237
<b>For sixteen years,</b>
<b>you ran away from what you did to mother.</b>

283
00:15:47,321 --> 00:15:50,366
<b>Now, I'll make sure you rot in prison!</b>

284
00:15:51,617 --> 00:15:53,369
<b>-[blows landing]</b>
<b>-[groaning]</b>

285
00:15:54,036 --> 00:15:55,371
<b>[Crisanto grunts]</b>

286
00:15:55,454 --> 00:15:56,997
<b>[scoffs]</b>

287
00:15:57,081 --> 00:15:59,875
<b>That damn woman's</b>
<b>been gone for a long time.</b>

288
00:15:59,959 --> 00:16:02,461
<b>And still, you can't let it go!</b>

289
00:16:03,087 --> 00:16:04,129
<b>[grunts]</b>

290
00:16:04,463 --> 00:16:05,422
<b>Come on!</b>

291
00:16:05,506 --> 00:16:07,091
<b>Fight back!</b>

292
00:16:07,174 --> 00:16:08,676
<b>Do it!</b>

293
00:16:08,759 --> 00:16:11,053
<b>You can't,</b>
<b>because your arm is missing!</b>

294
00:16:11,136 --> 00:16:14,640
<b>Now you finally know</b>
<b>what you made my mother feel!</b>

295
00:16:15,265 --> 00:16:17,226
<b>Now you know what I felt!</b>

296
00:16:17,851 --> 00:16:20,312
<b>-[grunts]</b>
<b>-[sullen music playing]</b>

297
00:16:20,396 --> 00:16:22,314
<b>Because of you, my brother is broken.</b>

298
00:16:23,065 --> 00:16:24,316
<b>You destroyed him!</b>

299
00:16:26,151 --> 00:16:28,112
<b>You ruined our lives!</b>

300
00:16:28,195 --> 00:16:29,863
<b>You killed her!</b>

301
00:16:30,614 --> 00:16:36,036
<b>[groaning]</b>

302
00:16:37,538 --> 00:16:40,833
<b>-[grunts]</b>
<b>-[groaning]</b>

303
00:16:40,916 --> 00:16:42,042
<b>You're alive.</b>

304
00:16:43,585 --> 00:16:45,546
<b>We thought you and your mother were dead.</b>

305
00:16:47,131 --> 00:16:49,091
<b>We thought Edong had killed you.</b>

306
00:16:50,342 --> 00:16:52,803
<b>We thought he would do the same thing.</b>

307
00:16:52,886 --> 00:16:56,515
<b>[foreboding music playing]</b>

308
00:16:58,058 --> 00:17:00,102
<b>[Theresa] </b><i><b>No!</b></i>

309
00:17:00,185 --> 00:17:02,354
<b>-[pitcher shatters]</b>
<b>-[Theresa wailing]</b>

310
00:17:02,438 --> 00:17:08,360
<b>-[sinister music playing]</b>
<b>-[Theresa panting]</b>

311
00:17:12,948 --> 00:17:13,991
<i><b>Oh, God…</b></i>

312
00:17:15,659 --> 00:17:16,660
<i><b>Please…</b></i>

313
00:17:17,703 --> 00:17:21,415
<b>[sobbing]</b>

314
00:17:21,498 --> 00:17:26,378
<b>[muffled sobbing]</b>

315
00:17:26,462 --> 00:17:28,130
<i><b>What did you do--</b></i>

316
00:17:28,213 --> 00:17:33,385
<b>[sinister music continues]</b>

317
00:17:33,969 --> 00:17:36,555
<i><b>My son…</b></i>

318
00:17:39,183 --> 00:17:41,602
<i><b>What did you do to my son?!</b></i>

319
00:17:41,685 --> 00:17:43,020
<b>[sobbing continues]</b>

320
00:17:43,103 --> 00:17:50,110
<b>[screaming, wailing in pain]</b>

321
00:17:50,194 --> 00:17:54,198
<b>[sinister music continues]</b>

322
00:17:54,281 --> 00:17:58,911
<i><b>What did you do to my son?!</b></i>

323
00:17:58,994 --> 00:18:01,163
<b>[sobbing]</b>

324
00:18:01,246 --> 00:18:04,625
<b>[Argie grunting weakly]</b>

325
00:18:07,669 --> 00:18:08,754
<i><b>Mama…</b></i>

326
00:18:08,837 --> 00:18:13,759
<b>[sinister music continues]</b>

327
00:18:13,842 --> 00:18:15,052
<b>[groans]</b>

328
00:18:15,135 --> 00:18:17,304
<i><b>You do not love your mother.</b></i>

329
00:18:17,387 --> 00:18:18,931
<b>[panicked breaths]</b>

330
00:18:19,014 --> 00:18:21,183
<i><b>If only you had spoken up sooner,</b></i>

331
00:18:21,809 --> 00:18:24,561
<i><b>none of this would have happened to her.</b></i>

332
00:18:24,645 --> 00:18:26,438
<i><b>What did you do to my mother?</b></i>

333
00:18:26,522 --> 00:18:28,899
<i><b>Where is Esther?</b></i>

334
00:18:28,982 --> 00:18:30,943
<i><b>What did you do to my mother?!</b></i>

335
00:18:31,026 --> 00:18:32,611
<b>[music intensifying]</b>

336
00:18:32,694 --> 00:18:34,029
<b>-[Edong grunts]</b>
<b>-[blow lands]</b>

337
00:18:34,738 --> 00:18:35,739
<b>[groans]</b>

338
00:18:37,533 --> 00:18:39,118
<b>-[blow lands]</b>
<b>-[body thuds]</b>

339
00:18:41,829 --> 00:18:45,874
<b>[ragged breaths]</b>

340
00:18:46,583 --> 00:18:48,127
<b>[gasps]</b>

341
00:18:49,545 --> 00:18:50,462
<i><b>She's in Bataan!</b></i>

342
00:18:51,421 --> 00:18:52,714
<i><b>In Dinalupihan…</b></i>

343
00:18:52,798 --> 00:18:55,384
<b>[sinister music continues]</b>

344
00:18:55,467 --> 00:18:56,468
<b>[Argie coughs]</b>

345
00:18:56,552 --> 00:18:58,011
<i><b>You got what you wanted.</b></i>

346
00:18:58,095 --> 00:18:59,388
<i><b>Let us live.</b></i>

347
00:19:00,055 --> 00:19:02,516
<i><b>Don't hurt us anymore. Just go away.</b></i>

348
00:19:02,599 --> 00:19:04,226
<b>[Argie crying]</b>

349
00:19:04,309 --> 00:19:06,186
<b>[breathing sharply]</b>

350
00:19:06,270 --> 00:19:08,814
<b>-[unsettling music playing]</b>
<b>-[choking]</b>

351
00:19:08,897 --> 00:19:12,901
<b>[groaning, coughing weakly]</b>

352
00:19:12,985 --> 00:19:14,862
<b>[panting]</b>

353
00:19:17,489 --> 00:19:18,574
<b>[Argie coughs]</b>

354
00:19:21,410 --> 00:19:25,956
<b>-[Edong grunts]</b>
<b>-[groaning]</b>

355
00:19:27,541 --> 00:19:29,334
<b>[Theresa grunting weakly]</b>

356
00:19:29,418 --> 00:19:36,008
<b>[panting, grunting]</b>

357
00:19:36,091 --> 00:19:43,015
<b>[dramatic music playing]</b>

358
00:19:48,270 --> 00:19:51,356
<b>[agonising scream]</b>

359
00:19:51,440 --> 00:19:53,192
<b>[breathing sharply]</b>

360
00:19:54,318 --> 00:19:55,861
<i><b>My son…</b></i>

361
00:19:55,944 --> 00:19:59,573
<b>[breathing heavily]</b>

362
00:20:02,618 --> 00:20:03,702
<i><b>Argie.</b></i>

363
00:20:04,077 --> 00:20:05,162
<i><b>Argie…</b></i>

364
00:20:06,079 --> 00:20:07,414
<i><b>Argie! Argie!</b></i>

365
00:20:07,497 --> 00:20:09,625
<i><b>Argie, my son!</b></i>

366
00:20:11,043 --> 00:20:12,586
<b>[wails] </b><i><b>Argie!</b></i>

367
00:20:12,669 --> 00:20:14,171
<i><b>Argie!</b></i>

368
00:20:14,254 --> 00:20:15,088
<i><b>Argie…</b></i>

369
00:20:15,172 --> 00:20:16,798
<i><b>Argie! Argie!</b></i>

370
00:20:16,882 --> 00:20:18,467
<i><b>Argie, my son!</b></i>

371
00:20:18,550 --> 00:20:20,177
<i><b>Son!</b></i>

372
00:20:20,802 --> 00:20:22,179
<i><b>Son?</b></i>

373
00:20:22,262 --> 00:20:23,889
<i><b>Oh God, son!</b></i>

374
00:20:23,972 --> 00:20:25,974
<i><b>Thank God you're alive!</b></i>

375
00:20:27,893 --> 00:20:31,605
<i><b>I thought I was going to lose you!</b></i>

376
00:20:31,688 --> 00:20:34,524
<b>[sobbing]</b>

377
00:20:34,608 --> 00:20:37,778
<i><b>Argie, my son!</b></i>

378
00:20:40,280 --> 00:20:43,367
<b>[Argie] But after I told</b>
<b>him where Aunty Esther was,</b>

379
00:20:43,450 --> 00:20:44,826
<b>he left immediately.</b>

380
00:20:47,329 --> 00:20:52,376
<b>We were so scared he might come back,</b>
<b>that we hid right away.</b>

381
00:20:53,335 --> 00:20:55,671
<b>I had no intention of showing myself.</b>

382
00:20:56,380 --> 00:20:59,883
<b>But when I found out that you found</b>
<b>Aunty Esther's body here…</b>

383
00:21:03,720 --> 00:21:06,306
<b>I know it's my fault that Edong found her.</b>

384
00:21:07,557 --> 00:21:10,686
<b>Argie, you had no choice back then.</b>

385
00:21:10,769 --> 00:21:13,230
<b>[unsettling music playing]</b>

386
00:21:13,313 --> 00:21:15,649
<b>I'm here to take my aunt's body.</b>

387
00:21:18,151 --> 00:21:20,237
<b>To give her a proper burial.</b>

388
00:21:21,947 --> 00:21:25,409
<b>I know my aunt made many mistakes,</b>
<b>but she's still my aunt.</b>

389
00:21:28,245 --> 00:21:31,623
<b>At least Mama supported and loved her.</b>

390
00:21:36,336 --> 00:21:37,337
<b>She's ready.</b>

391
00:21:37,421 --> 00:21:39,840
<b>You just need to</b>
<b>check and sign at the morgue.</b>

392
00:21:39,923 --> 00:21:41,133
<b>Let's go.</b>

393
00:21:45,971 --> 00:21:52,894
<b>[unsettling music continues, fades]</b>

394
00:21:54,604 --> 00:21:56,648
<b>Edong didn't kill them.</b>

395
00:21:56,732 --> 00:21:59,818
<b>-[dramatic music playing]</b>
<b>-Maybe we can still save him.</b>

396
00:21:59,901 --> 00:22:02,654
<b>-If he saw the presscon--</b>
<b>-He'll change his mind?</b>

397
00:22:03,530 --> 00:22:05,741
<b>He won't look for you,</b>
<b>he won't kill you anymore?</b>

398
00:22:07,534 --> 00:22:11,163
<b>He didn't kill Esther's sister or nephew,</b>

399
00:22:11,246 --> 00:22:13,332
<b>because they had nothing to do with you.</b>

400
00:22:14,124 --> 00:22:15,292
<b>But that was in the past.</b>

401
00:22:15,375 --> 00:22:17,002
<b>He's already dragged</b>
<b>so many people into this.</b>

402
00:22:18,295 --> 00:22:22,049
<b>[Marco] Dolores. Yuri. Steve.</b>

403
00:22:22,132 --> 00:22:24,134
<b>He even almost killed Seth.</b>

404
00:22:24,217 --> 00:22:26,386
<b>Were any of them</b>
<b>involved in him being locked up?</b>

405
00:22:26,470 --> 00:22:27,554
<b>No, right?</b>

406
00:22:28,680 --> 00:22:31,558
<b>With every killing and act of revenge,</b>

407
00:22:32,309 --> 00:22:34,603
<b>he just gotten worse, Erica.</b>

408
00:22:34,686 --> 00:22:36,563
<b>[Marco sighs]</b>

409
00:22:37,522 --> 00:22:39,399
<b>[Erica] </b><i><b>Edong, if you're watching…</b></i>

410
00:22:40,067 --> 00:22:42,402
<i><b>Free yourself.</b></i>

411
00:22:42,486 --> 00:22:47,324
<i><b>Not just for us,</b></i>
<i><b>but for you and your brother.</b></i>

412
00:22:48,784 --> 00:22:51,203
<i><b>We know among all of us,</b></i>

413
00:22:52,329 --> 00:22:54,831
<i><b>you were the most hurt by that tragedy.</b></i>

414
00:22:55,999 --> 00:22:59,795
<i><b>Even though we were</b></i>
<i><b>locked up by fear and shame,</b></i>

415
00:23:00,629 --> 00:23:02,923
<i><b>you suffered the most.</b></i>

416
00:23:04,299 --> 00:23:08,178
<i><b>But now, we're</b></i>
<i><b>trying to make things right.</b></i>

417
00:23:09,429 --> 00:23:11,264
<i><b>It's not too late, Edong.</b></i>

418
00:23:11,973 --> 00:23:14,142
<i><b>The story isn't over yet.</b></i>

419
00:23:14,935 --> 00:23:19,981
<i><b>We can still write an ending</b></i>
<i><b>where everything turns out good.</b></i>

420
00:23:20,690 --> 00:23:23,193
<b>Lying,</b>

421
00:23:23,860 --> 00:23:26,113
<b>comes with a price.</b>

422
00:23:27,155 --> 00:23:30,075
<b>Don't you understand that?</b>

423
00:23:30,158 --> 00:23:32,577
<b>Son of a bitch!</b>

424
00:23:33,036 --> 00:23:35,330
<b>Liars!</b>

425
00:23:36,206 --> 00:23:38,708
<b>You'll pay!</b>

426
00:23:39,835 --> 00:23:42,420
<b>[Edong] I'll make you all pay!</b>

427
00:23:44,131 --> 00:23:48,468
<b>[music becomes sinister]</b>

428
00:23:48,552 --> 00:23:51,429
<b>[both screaming in fear]</b>

429
00:23:51,513 --> 00:23:58,895
<b>[sinister music continues]</b>

430
00:24:12,159 --> 00:24:15,537
<i><b>I know it's impossible to</b></i>
<i><b>erase everything Mama said.</b></i>

431
00:24:15,620 --> 00:24:18,832
<i><b>But me, Erica, I celebrate</b></i>
<i><b>that you're still in this world.</b></i>

432
00:24:20,000 --> 00:24:22,335
<i><b>Am I a bad person for feeling relieved</b></i>

433
00:24:22,419 --> 00:24:25,130
<i><b>that he's there and not me?</b></i>

434
00:24:25,213 --> 00:24:26,840
<i><b>My father is Crisanto Santiago!</b></i>

435
00:24:26,923 --> 00:24:28,466
<i><b>You killed my mother!</b></i>

436
00:24:28,550 --> 00:24:30,719
<i><b>We said we want to start over.</b></i>

437
00:24:30,802 --> 00:24:33,263
<i><b>I can't even remember</b></i>
<i><b>what happened to me before.</b></i>

438
00:24:33,346 --> 00:24:35,307
<i><b>Everybody's already faced their demons,</b></i>

439
00:24:35,390 --> 00:24:37,058
<i><b>and I'm the only one left!</b></i>

440
00:24:37,642 --> 00:24:39,686
<i><b>-Aunty!</b></i>
<i><b>-There!</b></i>
